To be a grab member, points to qualify > 0 & need 2,200 points to redeem $5 off the next ride.  To be a silver member, points to qualify  > 3,000 & need 2,100 points to redeem $5 off the next ride.  To be a gold member, points to qualify > 9,000 & need 2,000 points to redeem $5 off the next ride.  To be a platinum member, points to qualify > 19,000 & need 1,900 to redeem $5 off the next ride.  Points work on a two-tier system. That is points are accumulated to move forward from one tier to the other.  Do take note that Tier ‘downgrades’ happen when you don’t earn enough points during Reward Period 1 or 2. For e.g. if you don’t earn enough points during Reward Period 1 (1 Jan – 30 June) to maintain your current tier, you will lose your tier and the privileges that come with it.  Points are available for all rides except grabhitch and grab shuttle.

To redeem $5 off a Grab ride: Member Tier: 2200 points Silver Tier: 2100 points Gold Tier: 2000 points Platinum Tier: 1900 points  The points can be accumulated from all Grab rides except GrabHitch and GrabShuttle. For every dollar spent, it converts into 1 point each and multiple by the mode of payment e.g. Cash or GrabPay. There are many other rewards available to redeem as well. The other day, I was able to redeem a free koi bubble milktea for just 100 points as I was a gold member. The rewards are easy to redeem and use!

Let’s talk about grab pay.   In Malaysia, for grab pay, RM 1 = 10 points (pts) So to get a Silver membership, you need 1000 pts, which means you need to spend RM100. (1000pts) For Gold membership, you need 3000 pts, which means you need to spend RM 300. (3000pts) For Platinum membership, you need 8000 pts, which means you need to spend RM800. (8000 pts)   So let’s talk about Singapore’s grab pay.   In Singapore, for grab pay, SGD1 = 16pts  So to get a Silver membership, you need 3000 pts, which means you need to spend SGD187.50. (3000pts) For Gold membership, you need 9000 pts, which means you need to spend SGD562.50. (9000pts) For Platinum membership, you need 19000 pts, which means you need to spend SGD1187.50. (19000 pts)   I would have easily gotten platinum membership if I am in Malaysia. Sadly, I am not. Based in SG  Took grab for a year ++ Spend around 700++ and sadly never will I get to Gold member or even platinum membership. I really hope that grab would do something about this. Maybe change the points system by letting us earn more points or maybe lower down the points for us to reach the membership. Thankyou.

Is all about contractual agreements between riders with UG and UG with drivers.  1) Contract between UG and Riders, is for UG to get the right car type to send rider from point A to B, but has UG done enough in rider booking app to ensure riders declare the mix of people taking the car? Since LTA and TP has such requirements, there is no wrong on UG to force riders to declare since is it a electronic service contract and the contract has to cover the drivers providing the service. Drivers has no contact and idea who are the riders before the booking and picking the riders, only UG has the mean to contact rider between themselves, more can be done before UG accepts rider's request and sending to drivers.  2) Contract between UG and drivers, is for drivers to fulfill jobs from UG to send their clients (riders) from point A to B. Right now drivers has zero ideas the mix riders they are picking until pickups, drivers should have the option to cancel the trip if the rider's mix is not as per LTA and TP requirements that cancellation should not impact their rating or incentives.  I am proposing that on rider's app, they have to declare if their rider mix has passenger below 1.35m and toddlers, if riders never declare but has such mix, the electronic service contract is consider null and void that driver's app should have the option to cancel without the fear of affecting their rating or incentives. In such cases, since driver already reached pick location and only to realize that riders falsely declared their rider mix, they can start the trip and end with special option indicating false rider declaration that a fee can be charged on rider for trip made to pick them. This will prevent riders from trying to book another car by falsely declaring rider mix.  Right now UG is making drivers or riders to communicate on LTA/TP requirements that has resulted in sour situations in who to cancel the trip if car cannot take the rider. All these are nonsenses, under the PHV new framework, UG has not done enough on ensuring right service to riders and riders both should be fined to if they insist on boarding a car that resulting in drivers caught breaking rules, else where is driver protection.

GrabShare is supposed to be shared rides for the grand objective to reduce cars in the roads and be green to environment.   Grab should actually only assign *matched* rides to drivers. If there's no match, the driver earns little because of the heavily discounted ride. Unmatched ride also defeats the spirits and grand purposes of ride sharing.   Try standing in the driver's shoes and you shall understand. The driver would have earned a higher  GrabCar fare for an unmatched GrabShare ride. Grab gives no options for them to opt out taking GrabShare jobs too.   This situation can be improved if Grab only assign *matched* GrabShare rides to drivers. And we are also aligning this service with its original grand purposes of reducing cars and greener to environment.  Another solution is to automatically revert the fare of an unmatched GrabShare ride to  GrabCar one upon completion of the job.

I would love take a GrabShare ride with Mr Khaw Boon Wan because he took up the challenge of the Transport Minister, a thankless job. Despite having a stroke in 2016, he recovered and continued his efforts by being on the ground as you can spot him taking public transport in the MRT trains. I bet he hasn't taken a GrabShare ride before though, would love to have him take up the challenge too so he can fully experience life as a typical Singaporean who doesn't own a car. It would be an honour to exchange conversation with him about how the public transport scene has changed with the rise of private hire and carpool services, and how quickly the country got around to building legal frameworks and regulations for the entire industry. We may be focusing on all the signal faults and train breakdowns, but we often overlook the other aspect of public transportation that has been made so easy and convenient for all of us.

Hi Grab, i have wrote in to grab about my encounter using grabshare last week but till date i have not receive any respond from any of your grabbers (23611908). Last week i took grab share with other passengers, and the ERP charge from the other passenger was charged to my account. Firstly, driver quietly deduct money under toll and others without telling me. This is very dishonest. Deduction of charges as such shuld be clearly communicated with the payers first isnt it? Secondly, the trip that required to pass through the ERP belongs to the other passenger hence it is  unfair to me to charge their ERP to my account. I seldom have to share a ride with another passenger when riding on GrabShare and recently when I did, the passenger was picked up from the same location as I.   As we were approaching the GrabShare car, we realized that we are sharing the same car and before getting into the car, we started a conversation to see who should sit in the front as there are 3 of us.  The driver himself got a little confused as we sat in the car as for Grabshare, the maximum number of passenger per ride is 2 persons and there are 3 of us.

I was the first passenger of a GrabShare ride. So I sat at the backseat. 100m into the journey, a ride was matched and the driver proceeded to fetch another passenger(s). Upon arriving at the location, I noticed there were two of them(a couple) so I volunteered to switch seats the the front seat. Maybe it was the gratuity that sparks our conversation since I was on the phone with my girlfriend regarding the recent balloting of a BTO. The couple gave me advices about applying for a flat, marriage, and holding banquet and stuff. They told me some proposal ideas too hahaha! Turned out that the driver also recently got married and I was the sole beneficiary of the conversation! It was a very interesting journey and all of us were very engaged to the extend even the driver overshot, neither of us complaint and was very understanding. Definitely the best ride ever! Thank you for pairing me with a loving couple and a kind driver!

I enjoy talking to people there was one incident where the grabshare passenger had to rush to hospital cos her father had to go for an operation but the gps showed tat i will be alighting first. I told the driver to alight her first as she seems in a distraught manner. Driver also waived the $3 late charges as she was rushing to get food for her mum whos waiting at the hospital. We calmed her down and was trying to make her not so panic. I understand the situation by sharing my experience about my dad who was hospitalised too for one month due to some infection. I just wanted to tell her that therr will be a point of time in life where things Don't go our way but with a lil bit of prayer n faith im sure everything will be fine. She alighted with tears on her eyes and said thank u for making her felt better during the ride.we became friends ever since. Its interesting to know the different people from all walks of life thru grabshare or grabhitch. A simple smile too would brightens up someone's day

I remembered taking this grabshare ride where I was the second rider and the man who sat with me was on the way to SAFTI while I needed to go to NTU to attend school. I had to rush to NTU first and he kindly allowed me to alight first although he should be the one alighting first! After realising that I am a student teacher, he told me about his fun stories when he was studying in NIE previously and he turned out to be my senior in school and we had the same professor for lessons! After that, we still exchanged contact and he would send me articles to read about educational policies :)

I took grab with my daughter and a lady joined us later. My daughter kept chatting with me and telling me how was her school day. She loved sharing all the "small things" and I hardly respond much but continue using my hp. The lady maybe noticed our "conversation" is only one sided... She then told my daughter that she has a little son back in oversea and she is on business in Singapore for 3 months. She mentioned that she missed her son so much and despite they chat on phone every night but she wishes she can hug him and gives him good night kiss before bedtime. Surprisingly my daughter gives the lady a pat on her arm and said "it's ok. Gor Gor (brother) will wait for you to come home." The lady hugged my daughter and said thank you. I smiled to the lady. Their conversation reminds me to cherish time with my daughter and do not take it for granted...

My GrabShare car arrived to pick up but I was already notified by the app that there was already a rider on it. As the car pulls up to me, I saw a pleasant looking lady with Tai Tai hairdo and her shopping bags on the back seat. I hesitated and decided to take the front seat when she suddenly took her shopping bags and placed them at her feet. I took it as a gesture to take the backseat with her.  She started talking about her shopping spree of branded goods. I asked whether she was local and she replied yes. I wanted to ask her what her hubby did for a living so she could live a Tai Tai lifestyle but I dared not...  Upon pulling up to her luxury condo somewhere near Orchard Road, I remarked that the place looked exquisite with waterfalls and mini garden patches. She said it indeed was and she pointed to me that the sheltered open space was great for hanging around as it was cozy and airy.   I then plucked up the courage to ask her what her husband's job was that made her live a life of a Tai Tai. She smiled, told me that it was her who paid for most of her condo purchase, and invited me to tea sometime and she would tell me more then.  After she alighted and waved goodbye to me, the car drove me off. I looked at the namecard: MLM company director leading one of the largest teams of her company locally, South East Asia, and China.

For me, it happen in the ubi area where I had grabshare after work to get home. The next rider whom was sharing with me was pick up @ComfortDrivingSchool at ubi. Was a young slender girl probably in her easy 20s. She was looking low and worried. I went on to start a conversation which I'm sure has change her perspective about failing her upcoming driving test to having to pass her upcoming driving test. We talked about strategies that can help her better manage the circuits that she's worried about like how to  drive through an S-course without mounting kerb etc. This conversation aroused the grab car driver's and he also started giving her pointers.   It's not just a rider that I befriended, it's a moment that has probably lift up someone confidence. Don't u agree.

I once took a grab to school and the driver informed there will be another passenger joining us from my block. There was once when I was using grab share to town area  and a lady of around my age was already in the car when the car arrive. I took a grabshare with my friend and at that time, changing of locations/two locations wasn't allowed. I met a co-rider and I shared with him how I have save $2000 a month by selling away my car and taking grab everyday. We talked about how this sharing economy has helped so many people. People who are in between job, people who are stressed with their daily work, people who are willing to go an extra mile to make more every month. A car sitting in a carpark for 8 hours a day is now driven by someone who is willing to work hard and put the vehicles to work hard too. There are some many great think about sharing economy, lesser carbon, more efficiency and cheaper cost of living. Mobike and ofo and all the delivery services are great technology that encourage sharing economy

I took GrabShare and the other person boarded the car at the same office building with me. I was on a grabshare ride to SGH when i was matched to a second rider at East Coast Lagoon. The rider was an American lady who has been in Sg for a few months. My favorite hidden Kopitiam is in Prime Bizhub woodlands. It's literally hidden because there's no bus that leads to it. Nearest bus stop is 1km away, no MRT, only by car. And it's along Woodlands Ave 12 (Expressway Exit). Even people who live in Woodlands for years rarely knows about this place. Ironically they serves the best 24Hr DimSum at only $1.20 and one of the most authentic Bak Kut Teh in town. Visit them after 10pm you can enjoy the whole kopitiam to yourself enjoying the Dim Sum and drinks.

Chin Mee Chin - hainanese coffee shop along East coast road. A morning slurp of its aromatic kopi coupled with kaya toast nicely charred with thick slurp of butter and heavenly kaya. Top that of with soft boiled eggs, kickstart a wonderful weekend! shop has custard puffs etc too. Grab me there!!!

Heap Seng Leong the warm mouldy coffeeshop with no ventilation. You need willpower to sit indoors watching the uncle in old pyjama pants making your kopi through the traditional sock. The butter kopi is best in Singapore and I have it only once a year for the sake of my cholesterol. Not a hangout for the faint-hearted or heat-sensitive.

Fair View Food Court - 371A Woodlands Avenue 1.. this kopitiam is goodie good.. best among the woodlands area.. serve the best claypot gong bao diced chicken with rice, good savouring Hokkien mee, the traditional western food, and the mouth watering zichar!!! I alway cannot make my choice whenever i m there!!

My favourite hidden Kopitiam is really a hidden kopitiam in the Tan Tock Seng hospital.  This is quite a specious kopitiam not only there is a huge section reserved area for the hospital workers also the foods stores  options selling a healthier alternatives foods but still taste deliciously.  I personally like the Chicken rice , Japanese & the very nice cold and hot desserts stores.

My favorite hidden Kopitiam is Da Zhong Cafe (大众茶室) in Hainanese Village Food Centre (Lorong Ah Soo/ Hougang). It serves authentic, traditional coffee and tea. The boss makes an effort to ensure that every cup of coffee and tea is freshly brewed. Their coffee is rich and heavy, and has a nutty taste.

My favourite Kopi Tiam is a old  old shop near Potong Pasir b cos their full of loving ppl n young time memories with my parents ,n when he is around he used to order a Kopi wif butter on TOP of it to make coffee more fragile to wake mi up b for I go to work , I love my parents

Have to be at Blk 37 Japan Rumah Tinggi!!! The neighborhood gives you all the nostalgia feel you love ❤️. Old school bus interchange that you cannot find anywhere else. Most importantly, awesome Kopi and Teh Tarik and kaya toast plus all local food that we all like. Also ample parking lots for those who drive.

Chin Mee Chin. My Mother used to bring me there for their kaya bread and coffee after visiting my grandmother at the nearby nursing home years ago. After my grandma passed on I had not visited it since.

My Hidden Kopitiam is Killiney Kopitiam at Changi Airport terminal 1.Why I choose that kopitiam is I feel the size of the kopitiam is quite big and with many ppl going there for coffee there is a good reason to believe that they have nice tasting toast and good and reasonable priced coffee and tea.I also think for a modern coffee shop to be set up at the airport it allows both passengers who are boarding the planes or those who just arrive in singapore to enjoy a cup of coffee and toast to curb their hunger for those who does not drink starbuck too and anyone who goes to the airport can chill at the place.Although it is a modern coffee shop whenever I drink the coffee it makes me feel a sense of going back to when life was simple and it make me feel like having a sense of familyfeeling and warmth feeling!!In addition, after drinking coffee we can spend time walking ard the airport just relaxing and enjoying the changi airport environment!!#grabsg#passengerpick

Best hidden kopitiam is the one near my house at block 787 cck north 5 because it has the best yong tau fu!!!!! The guys make their own ingredients and they also have tofu lor mee! Prata is awesome. Wanton mee is awesome. Idk how to convince you guys more
Dong Po Colonial Cafe at Kandahar Street.. Rather "hidden" n inconvenient for me.. Love this place.. The old school kopitiam with old school cakes.. 😋
My favorite hidden kopitiam is Sungei Road laksa, every time need take MRT and change bus walk 10 minutes. Need one hour traveling time to reach.
Heap Seng Leong. It is the only few left for a kopitiam of its kind. Has old school vibes and the Kopi Gu Yu (Butter Coffee) is awesome.

Good Good Eating House @ 24 Sixth Avenue.   Their big watery egg yolks coupled with bread & Horlicks make the bad bad me a bit "good good". ◡̈   There re other nice breakfast choices there too! Enjoy! #SharingIsCaring #passengerspick #grabsg
Tong Ah Eating House at Keong Saik  Road. Old school Thick Kopi kosong with one of the best Kaya toast and the soft boiled eggs. Always feel relaxed slurping the kopi.

If you ride or drive with Uber, Grab or Ryde, you're warmly  invited to join this new group. The main purpose is to share common problems and experiences from both sides of the car sharing experience. Our admins are newbies so forgive us for the bare look and feel. Member content is varied and hopefully focused to achieve a better ride experience for all parties.  https://www.facebook.com/groups/1013566295436747/

It'd be great if you could take this seriously and provide your super regular customers with a much better service.

I sat in my dad’s living room reading one night while he watched television. An hour passed before I realised it, and I felt bad for not speaking during that time. I asked if he was OK, and he said yes. Then I apologized for not talking more.Dad replied. “Talking is like ketchup. If you like the meat enough, you don’t need the ketchup—and if you like the company enough, you don’t need the conversation.” My dad never earned a college degree, but he was the smartest person I ever knew.

My dad has always - literally always, put himself before me. Be it bringing me to the doctor when I was younger despite having a toothache (which later result in him having to remove the tooth), or fetching me home from school on late nights even when he's at the other end of Singapore, I'm the first on his list. This Father's Day, I'd like to take the opportunity to just spend some good father-daughter time with him to make up for all the lost time. Nothing fancy, just a good chat over a proper meal. :)

My dad he's a selfless person. He doesn't ask for anything from me and my siblings,he just wants the best for us. He never complains regarding our life situation when problems keep adding on and on instead he will try to make it work and ensure that his family has food on the table and is happy even when he knows he has little money left to suffice through the month. After my grandfather passed away,he doesn't talk much but i try to create a conversation with him like how he does with his dad. To have someone to talk to as he has not much friends. I am grateful to have him as my dad as he's my role model and my hero. He teaches us to be humble,responsible and disciplined. So this father's day,i would like to show him my appreciation by bringing him somewhere and have a good father-son bonding time. 😌

My dad is one wonderful and selfless man! He always put others first and he only skimps on himself and not others. Since his retirement, he has been taking care of our daily dinners. He never fail to surprise us with new dishes that not only looks good but taste great! He is a perfectionist! Always exploring new recipes and perfecting his cooking skills! When my children or any of us falls sick, he will automatically prepare a pot of porridge. He is such a detailed, thoughtful and kind man. He remembers every of our favourite dishes. It's the little things that he does that I appreciate so much which so often overlooked by others. 2. It's been many years since he has retired, he is already out of touch with most his staffs, clients and suppliers. It would be great to make a surprise gathering/party inviting all these people for him to have a catch-up.

I'm grateful for to my dad for giving my Brother and I the best that he could. Growing up, we were never rich, we never went on holidays but yet we always had whatever we wanted. Dad worked hard to provide for the family. Maybe we never had the best things, as compared to others, but we never felt that we lost out on anything. It was always work and home... all for us.  Dad loves Cycling now and he loves going on overseas scenic Cycling trips. I hope to go with him on one of these trips... with the whole family.. tho we can't Cycle as far and as fast as him but I think to be able to cycle as a family would be awesome!

My dad, my 1st hero in my life. He is a selfless man who put his family and kids in the first place.  He skimps on himself but give us the best he could. He does not much education but he try his best to work thru his ranks and provide the best he could give us especially things he did not have when he was a kid. During my growing years, he spends many years protecting the country working overseas, but our relationship remains strong because he works for the family and the country we loved. And now having semi-retired, his daily joy is to see my  baby daughter daily after work. For this yr father's day (which is also his first time being a grandfather), I would like to bring him for a ride around Singapore to explore Singapore like a tourist and explore those foods that he loves when he was younger.

My dad.... was a man who believes in helping in household chores.... even after so many years ... I still remember my dad helped me with the household chores on Saturdays and Sundays... being eldest girl ... although I had 3 elder brothers...my mum made I clean the house and washed the clothes and cooked rice for my siblings... this is a typical Indian mother's mentality.... girl have to do the household chores.... but my dad always helped me with all the chores on Saturday and Sundays .,, coz it was his day off... he made sure I had full rest on the weekends... he made sure the house is sparkling clean including the toilets... I have learnt from him how a house and it's toilet should be....As it reflects on the people who are living there.... even now I don't have a helper to help me clean my house.... even in his last years he made sure the house is always clean.... I just wonder how many men would do this for their children besides earning income for the family....I miss my dad so much....

I hardly know anything abt my dad as he passed away when I was six months old.   Though he wasn't around when I grew up, I could feel him around not physically but nentally and spiritually by seeing around me of my siblings and his siblings.   My mum would bring me to his grave every few months until late teens and she shared her life with him along the way to the graveyard.    Her stories inspired me to know more about how responsible my father was. He work hard enough to give the family a shelter. His strictness secured the respect of his siblings  He was also an orphan as me and with sheer determination brought 2 families to another greater levels.He is rare and he deserved the merit of respect.

Being an teenager, i think my dad knows i would definitely rebal him in any ways i could. My parents divorce when i was very young, hence i do not know what really happen between. Just knew that i was force to move out and separate from my dad since young. When i start become older, my mum couldnt control and let me do what i wanted. This is where my dad comes into my life. Each and every year during festive season he would call me and ask me to have dinner together. During my birthday he would bring me go eat good food. When i turn 18th, i went and get my "visible" tattoo. And from then, my tattoo become more and more visible become more and more position. One day he told me he would like to talk and this when he told me all the hardship he had went thru to make sure i get a good life even thou i am not living with him anymore. He told me the ups and down he encounter and the future ups and down he and I would encounter. My dad has play a really big part of my adulthood life. With helping me to cope with stress at work to giving me suggestion on work issue. This year has been an tough year for me and him aa we had just gotten our new house and we would have to fork out a huge sum of amount to make the house what we wanted. But because he is not earning much neither do I, we would have to save and save before we could renovate the house to what we like. Despite all this, my dad kept pushing money to me, kept making sure that i am surviving well and that i do not miss a single meal. With this, he is the greatest man in the world.

With Grab's new multi-stop ride feature, Alan planned a meaningful outing to bring his French friend to visit the famous local icon- Merlion. His friend has stayed over his place the night before, so both woke up early that day and had breakfast at the Coffeeshop below Alan's block. Before leaving, Alan dapaoed teh peng to see his French friend's jaw dropped when he saw the tea being drunk from a plastic bag... 'Gosh.... eeks..... oh no, this reminds me of the hospital.....'. Alan burst out laughing & said, 'Please Alfonso, don't say that to the many uncles you'll see drinking tea or coffee this way.....' At this point, Alan took out his phone and opened the iconic green & white Grab app. The default address of his home is already reflected, so his entered 'Merlion Park' at the destination. Just then, with a smirk grin, he tapped the additional stop icon and entered '147 Sims Avenue'. 'Done! Let's head for the Merlion!' While waiting for their Grab car to come, Alan took out his phone and called someone 'Hello Uncle! Ya, Alan here, I called last night to order the durian. Ya ya.... Vacuum pack like the other time. ok! Can can, I reaching in about 15 mins. Ok.... thank you ah, Uncle!' Alfonso stared at Alan upon hearing the word 'Durian'..... 'Due... rain?' 'yup, u come Singapore must eat durian.... very famous fruit...not cheap too... but it's ok, I treat you.... We'll pick up the durian on our way to the Merlion.' 'Oh... alright...' '6745L.... ah.... there, our car is here, come Alfonso!' Both guys hoped onto the red 6745L and started their touristy day..... they picked up their durian, reached Merlion Park, took photos, talked, laughed and pointed here and there..... then when their stomachs growled, Alan whipped out the durian and they sat down with Alan grabbing his share of the heavenly fruit, only to see Alfonso almost chocked by the smell..... Alan cried out laughing again but managed to persuade Alfonso to try the fruit.... Alfonso almost vomited & kindly rejected another bite, to which Alan grinned and said 'Oh well.... then I'm gonna finish them all..... you sure ah, you don't want?' 'No... no.. no.., thanks...' grumbled Alfonso before dashing off to take even more photos of the vomiting sea creature instead..... 😊

Always your little girl 🙆 . A mother is the truest friend we have, the one who sticks with us through ups and down, go the extra mile to protects us, who shelters us when it gets dark and gloomy and celebrate your joys with the purest of heart. You never have to doubt her, because she is the one that loves you most and that is something that will never change.. for she is your mother . I never really realised how much I depended on my mother until I went on exchange. All my life, she has stuck by me and helped me through every life obstacle. From waking me up every morning to fetching me back home after a long day of school/work, she was always one step ahead so that we could have a comfortable life! Even as I set out on my 6months long exchange, she heavy-heartedly helped to pack my luggage and stuffed it full with all the instant local mixes you could find . Nearer to the date, she even surprised me by booking a flight just to follow me  and help me settle in "I'm old enough to handle this on my own mum..." I told her but she insisted. When I was there, I remembered feeling slightly annoyed that she was still "bossing" me around and nagging about safety... "I can't wait for her to leave" I thought to myself . . Oh but I was so wrong. As her departure date grew closer, I started to get more anxious. Finally the day came and as I waved goodbye to her at the train station, I looked into her soft gentle eyes and something in me caved in. Tears started to well up in my eyes. I was overwhelmed with emotions and this sudden panic about being without my mum! As she turned away from me, her smile dropped and for the first time I saw her sadness. That broke me completely and I burst into wild tears. Immediately, I dropped everything and chased madly after her. Crashing into her and hugging her really tight, "Don't go!" I cried as I tried my best to burrow into her soft embrace again. "I love you..." . I will never forget that moment. Nothing will ever compare to a mother's love and I am grateful for my mother, who have always stuck by me though good and bad times. I love you Mummy . . . Thank you #grab @Grab for this opportunity to #ridingwithmumsg #mum #love #forever

Riding with Mum through my Life journeys versus riding together with Grab?  Honestly, Mum, from a humble background, never travels in a taxi nor gives me an opportunity to travel together in a cab as it is too costly n we must save for 'rainy days'!  So we always travel together by buses.   At a tender age. I always accompanied Mum wherever she went: to the market, temples or visiting relatives till my marriage in Sep 1977. We were very very close!  The old photo showed me, a young sweet girl at 14 with Mum at Ah Gong's house at Albert Street, after an hour journey from my kampong at Bukit Teresa. We had to walk 20 mins to the bus-stop but surprisingly then, I never complained because it was fun being with your loved one! When young, I don't resemble Mum. :)  The newer photo was taken last Jul at Alive Museum to celebrate Mum's birthday with my Dad and two Brothers. One Brother was the chauffeur then.  We chose Alive Museum because we wanted our parents to try being creative; to pose with whatever there! Something parents had never done before.   Indeed, it was really fun seeing Mum laughing loudly there.  But I still loved this photo best of all. The backdrop of a BIG RED LOVE of leaves gave me the courage to tell Mum the three golden words 'I LOVE YOU!'  That was our glorious moments!   At their twilight years (86 and 91) for the past seven years, we have weekly outings to the movies, shopping malls followed by lunch. We know that they look forward to these.  Take a closer look at this photo. Now at 62, I really resemble Mum: our size and full round faces!   Hope to win free JustGrab rides to change her mindset: that the cab rides are very comfortable especially for their ages, very convenient, very fast and actually affordable!   Pampering Mum with a bouquet of carnations, cake or dinner are pretty common but blessing  her with free taxi rides is INDEED UNIQUE!  She's a special Mum so she deserves special moments!  Thank you, Mom: for giving me the gift of life, caring diligently for me as a premature baby and teaching me patiently moral values, nursed me often when I had very bad asthmatic attacks especially in the middle of the night. Yet not a word of complaint nor thought of abandoning this baby/child and your SLEEPLESS NIGHTS didn't affect your cherry performance the next day as a housewife and Mum to five kids. Kudos to you, Mum!  When I lost my first foetus followed by 6 months of aggressive treatments in 1978, you were there with me, for me, urging me to be optimistic and to nourish me well you cooked delicious meals for me as this was my 'confinement month'! My world nearly collapsed then!  It was you who tenderly and slowly guided me through my  life's most difficult period! My depressive and crying bouts, for months, must have worried you terribly, yet you forced herself to put on a brave front for my sake! Thank you, Mum for being my PILLAR OF SUPPORT and riding with me through my deepest LOW in life!  Your unconditional selfless love, cheerful disposition, and forgiveness for my mistakes, greatly touched me!  There were times when I was disobedient and drove you up the wall, yet you patiently explained to me after your punishment.  How could I not improve to be a better person to repay your love and kindness?  I controlled my temper and learnt from you the virtues of patience, tolerance and perseverance. These are your strength. Your good characteristic traits!   No wonder people commented that MOTHER'S LOVE IS THE GREATEST IN THE WORLD! ❤️❤️  Mom, I am proud of you, elated to have you as my Mom and never ever will trade you for other woman!  Now, in your twilight years, it's my turn to cherish and support you anytime!  HAPPY MOTHER'S DAY!  TO MY SUPERMOM!  My WONDERWOMAN!  Let's grab this opportunity to ride Grab taxi FOR FREE! Cheers!!  Thanks for your fabulous giveaway! To pamper the most important WOMAN in my life!  Liked and shared.  #ridingwithmumSG  Phuong Tô  Tang Xiao Rong  Rachel Hor  Bernard Lai

More than 40 years ago I was still a scrawny girl living in a poor country side in Fujian ,China and mum did a lot of chores like tiling the land,feeding the fowls,growing and watering the crops,picking and selecting seeds for sowing again to ensure optimum growth of cash crops for sale to feed the family.              With the hardship experienced,Mum developed and instilled in me too such good traits as kindness,compassion and dedication for which she earned everyone's respect from the countryside we once lived.                Time flies like the flicked pages of a book as I am now happily married and have become a Simgapore Citizen together with mum.              Time has changed my face and mum's face too but it has not changed our love for each other.  I am  now the proud mother of a 8 year old boy and glad that at least I am doing a small part of National Service by contributing to the dwindling Singapore's population.I may opt for more children in line with Singapore Government's procreation policies and of course not forgetting mum's ever ready assistance.  Thank you Mum for taking this long ride all the way from China and accompanying me and finally making this little red dot our beloved country for all of us to sink our roots here.  Mum I hope to win so that being a very thrifty person you will  complain no more about the high transport cost when moving about in Singapore and this is made possible with the compliments of Grab.  #ridingwithmumSG

Dearest Mum,               I have long wanted to express my heartfelt gratitude and sincerest appreciation for what for what you have done for me ,for my family and this little red dot.         In the 1960/1970s, you had to take on several jobs--seamstress,an amah,going from street to street picking old cans/bottles and used clothings for sale and peddling homemade food like nasi-lemak and kueh kueh. You did all those jobs just to supplement dad's meagre as a manual worker.You had no eduaction but you could teach us to distinguish between right and wrong, support and encourage  us in our studies and all your five children have  always excelled in their studies and graduated from universities holding respectable jobs-lawyer,engineer,system manager and tutor attributed mainly to your efforts and diligence .            You donate  generously to temples, mosques and churches without discrimination and stress the importance of racial and ethnic tolerance and mutual respect for one another-a key criterion for survival of Singapore.              You imbue in me to visit old folks home, orphanages and shelter homes for ex-drug addicts/offenders to cheer and bring hope and financial assistance whenever possible.               You  babysit for our neighbours' kids and elderly folks,sew their clothes and provide groceries and food to those in need.You love to whip up your favourite curry chicken,chicken rice,poh piah,cakes and desserts and invite friends,acquaintances and neighbours for the kampung spirit get together atmosphere.  Mum,thank you for everything you have done for the me ,the neighbours and the community and I hope the generous sponsor /organiser Grab will reward you as you have gone beyond helping and encouraging me as you are also the pride of our neighbours,the community and also our Nation being the pioneer generation, you are really that "Here For Me"  who deserves a treat for your contributions from Grab as you have touched many lives too and this May is also your Diamond Wedding Anniversary to our beloved dad so I hope to win this reward for you .  The left photo here is more than 50 years ago when you carried a helpless toddler like me then but today thanks to your upbringing,I am successful in my own ventures and happily married with a daughter which is also your favourite grandaughter so it is now my turn to take good care of you and thank you for being my greatest driver throughout our life journeys because without you we are like passengers without destination-- On behalf of my siblings I want to wish you❤❤❤❤ HAPPY MOTHER'S DAY❤❤❤❤❤❤❤ and thank you Grab again for organising such a meaningful contest. #ridingwithmumSG

Sounds like Grab is taking after Uber's methodology...  But may I add that there should be an avenue for Drivers to repudiate any 2 stars or below ratings. Reason being some riders can be a little too harsh or vindictive, counting every little infraction against the driver. A driver ought to be able to refute any accusations of unsafe or unprofessional ratings as it will eventually count against the driver and may end up in his/her termination.  While I understand it is "industry practice" to protect the rider's anonymity so as to encourage a better rate of participation in giving Drivers ratings, the anonymity could also unfortunately be grossly unfair for the driver.  While I also agree that  high frequency of Low ratings will stand to prove the driver's unprofessionalism, the fact that a single 1 star rating can already adversely affect the driver's overall standing and reputation.

Hi everyone! Thank you so much for sharing your "More for Less" stories. The contest has officially ended. We will be reaching out to the 5 winners real soon. Stay tuned to our page in the next few days as we’ll be sharing with you how to ball on a budget!

One fine morning, I was having some beers with my buddy Jason Teo whom I will hereon refer to as Ahteo. Yes it was the morning but just to be clear, we took a grabcar to the bar. We were getting really high on Guinness and Ahteo came up with a brilliant idea of pretending to be a woman to impress the waiter so maybe we can get more beers! When you're having beers, naturally everything you hear sounds like a bloody good plan. So I got him to stand up and he tucked in his shirt and we had to find a way to hide the bulge in his pants. I suggested a tape but Ahteo looked down and realized it was just his stuff that was parked wrongly. So he did a good squat and the bulge was gone. Then I went on cutting pieces of paper in the shape of spaghetti. We stuck all that on his head and crumpled more papers into balls and put them under his shirt. He looked absolutely hideous. But we went for it anyway. He did a sweet dogwalk into the bar and tried his best to seduce the bartender. Obviously, he was ignored and was brushed off as a regular drunkard just roaming around trying to find meaning in life. And then Ahteo came up with another idea to seduce him. He started softly singing Beyond's greatest hit, Hai Kuo Tian Kong.   "Gam tin ngoh hon ye lui hon seuit piu gwoh waai jeuk laang keuk liu dik sam woh piu yuan fong....."  The bartender froze. Ahteo started smiling. The bartender turned and as I slowly walked towards Ahteo, I started seeing teardrops down the bartender's cheek. It was happening. What initially came off as the stupidest plan for anyone to come up with, was actually working! I inched closer and the bartender slid his hands past the bartop, grabbed a bottle of whiskey and broke it on Ahteo's head! I was startled! What an unexpected yet interesting turn of events! It was rather clear that the plan has burnt to ashes now. Ahteo was screaming in pain while the bartender started yelling "HOW DARE YOU SPOIL THE BEST SONG EVER CREATED" and well, I didn't have much of a choice but to agree with him as in all honesty, Ahteo ruined the song. The bartender calmed down, came over to us, helped Ahteo up. We put him on a chair and wrapped his head with the papers we used for his fake breasts. The bartender apologized for breaking the bottle on his head and wasting all the whiskey. He knew we hated to waste them. Ahteo hugged him and they both had a small funeral for the whiskey that was poured. Following that, we had free flow Guinness all night. We paid only $10 a pint each and I drank for $1000. Well, Ahteo drank about $1000 worth of cider instead because after the stunt he pulled off, he found out he actually liked dressing up as a woman.   We got more for less! Ahteo's head wasn't worth anything since it's empty anyway.

One day when I planned for a mother-daughter outing with Ruby, we decided to have lunch at a particular BBQ/grill place which changes their menu every other day based on whatever's fresh. Fast-forward after eating and when we were paying the bill, we were charged with a random 20% discount off our bill. Sure, why not take it right? So out of curiousity, I questioned the cashier on why did we get a discount? She said "oh because the chef said the lobsters were not as fresh today. So we can't compromise on quality." We paid less and we got the full grill menu of that day with 20% off, win! #BallinWithGrab #MoreForLess

So here goes, my partner in crime, Lexy Lim and I were eating at a particular restaurant for a buffet one evening. When we were done with our buffet, we wanted to pay the bill and continue shopping because food coma. One of the floor staff then told us “hey did you know we actually have a Groupon deal right now? the deal is 40% off leh, each of you buy 1 and it will be much cheaper” Being cheapskates like everyone knows, we went on Groupon and purchased the coupon immediately, went to the cashier and voila. Literally, more for less. #BallinWithGrab #MoreForLess

I usually shop online for groceries with Gwen on a particular online supermarket. So when we were done with our shopping, we decided to check out and pay the full bill. Couple of days later, when our items were delivered to our place, we found that we got double quantities of our items! Paid 100% of the bill and got so much more. Can’t say no to free food supplies! 😄#BallinWithGrab #MoreForLess

Date nights/day outs in Singapore CAN get pretty expensive and most couples would attest to this. So any opportunity to get more bang for our buck would definitely be utilised.  On one particular "date day out", we'd single-handedly managed to accomplish 3 activities without forking out a single cent (not including public transport!)  1: Watching a weekend movie (courtesy of me winning an internal company award and scoring movie tickets, yeeeeba!)  2: A public exhibition (and a pretty interesting one at that coz it was about defence) and finally,  3: A FREE dinner (the ultimate clincher, please don't stop reading). So after dinner and in our haste to get home to catch the last train (all you last train folks, I'm sure ya feel me 😂), we hurriedly settled the bill without looking and raced to the station. But I had a niggling feeling there was something weird with the numbers. While we were on the train home, I was looking at the receipt and found out why - the restaurant had undercharged us by accident! >.< My SO then piped up, "Actually, that dinner was also free coz I paid for it with the $10 we picked up at Sentosa last week" 😂😅  So number 3 honestly isn't the best highlight (coz I do still feel bad!) but this Date Day Out was truly #MoreForLess.   cc Shawn Goh my fave partner-in-crime 😘. now everyone knows how cheap we are! hehehhe #sayitloudsayitproud #pigebuaytahan #cheepcheap 😂 also, #BallinWithGrab !!!

There was once Jaime Lee thought that her Grabdriver was adorable and he was "totally my type". She terrorized him by asking him to text me, otherwise she would rate him one star. (She was kidding btw) But well, he texted me and admitted that this was one of his most interesting rides ever. #ballinwithgrab Anyway, the point is Grab was cheaper than Uber/normal cabs at the point of time, plus we made a new friend. #moreforless

Recently, we ordered some stuff from Amazon and there was a delay in delivery by a week. I emailed them to explain the situation. Under goodwill, they delivered another set of what I ordered in 4 days! And guess what, they delivered by original order the following week. Woohoo... I got an extra set  of  everything for me and my friend! Such a delightful service by Amazon. Love getting more for less. :D #moreforless With Eunice Ho. :)

Last Dec, There were 8 of us and its too Lehchey to flag for a cab, thus we used grab taxi service.. And, we ALL managed to fit into a normal taxi!! Best of all, with the $15 discount, our trip was totally free!  Wondering why 8 of us can fit into 1 taxi? Coz its 4 pregnant ladies!!  We definitely got More for Less! All the best to us Cindy Chan

Alicia Chua and I went to Adventure Cove recently. We added up the entrance fee, locker rental and food pricing; and from there calculated how many times of each ride must we take in order to make our money's worth! The thrilling rides were worth $2, while the tamer rides were $1. In all we took 20+ times of all the rides, to compensate for the $40 we paid 😂 Not exactly an example of going budget, but getting more bang for my buck!

So you know how hotels love using taglines like “Stay More For Less”? Well, this is a story of my partner in crime and I getting literally the most out of our staycay.   So ZL and I booked a Deluxe Room at a particular hotel along Tanjong Pagar, and right before we checked in, we were told that the rooms were fully booked and we were unable to proceed with our check-in. We were then frustrated because we did have a print-out of our actual booking - we showed it to the hotel and…they felt like they had to compensate us for this and they immediately settled us in to a DELUXE SUITE which was at least 2x more of what we originally paid on the booking site. Talk about getting more for less??? It doesn't get any better than this. #BallinWithGrab

There was once when me and my friends Ben Cheong Corey Chang and "you know who you are" went for break during class. There was this Japanese bento stall at the ground floor and they were selling their leftover yakitori for $5. All of them did not bring their wallet and i was the only one with wallet. So they beg me for the $5. I gave it to them and we sweep all the leftovers for $5. #brokestudents #discountjustsweeponly   After we bought the leftovers, they only ate abit and so we had no choice but to throw them away. Shortly after we threw the food away, one of them said he/she was hungry. Dafug?! We went to Changi Village after that.   Yes guys. #stillsouroverit #moreforless #orsoithought

Me and my colleague Datou Tan always need to do overtime, how do we get more for less? Ever since the introduction of grabshare, we are so happy! Because we share the cost of the ride together as we live in the same area. The money we save from grabshare, we pool together and treat ourselves a sumptuous meal when we accumulate enough money! Hope this scheme will continue forever and really love all the promotion codes!

More for less?  Blessed to have it All the time!  Grabbed Grab offers for Ng and I many times, rain or shine, rush or leisure, pay 2 for the price of 1, extra pockets for more rides, forge new friendships, opportunities & life lessons. All in one price. 😄  Huge gains, isn't it?

Bryan Tan Jun Han We're all about good food for good value. So when we discovered groupon we were overjoyed! There were always vouchers for sale for like 40% or  50% off. What more could we ask for? Then my boyfriend introduced me to shopback. This allowed the money spent on groupon vouchers to earn cash back as well. Whatttttt? Discounts on discount vouchers? It gets even better. Whenever Grab comes out with a promo code, we'll always remember to exploit it to the max. Sometimes a 5 dollar promo code would mean a 2 dollar grabshare ride to the restaurant. That's what I would call getting bangs for my buck. #BallinWithGrab

How do we get more for less? I always partner up with my best friend Seline Tan and we always wait for airfare or cruise promotions such as one for one  and we really save alot! The money saves on the fares can be channelled to other purchases! We pay less but we gain so much more! Thanks GRAB for this awesome giveaway!

On our visit to USS Ng Zuxiang bought us ponchos for a water ride. Instead of throwing them away after that day, he has kept it and reused it quite a few times... Embarrassing but he says why not? There's a sentimental feeling to it. 😂 one poncho, multiple usage. #BallinWithGrab #MoreForLess
Juliana Ng and I were greedy as usual and we ordered lots of food at the restaurant. The owner gave us a free dish with our meal #economical #ordermoreforless
The best ride is always #FREE! Totally FOC after using Promo code! We took the ride from Vivocity to my house and its FREE! Hehehe #SoShiok! Jerry Sng

Several years ago like at least 15yrs by now, me and my partner Eddie Lim went to marina bay open air bbq. We frequent this place alot. If u still remember those stretch of open air bbq near the marina bowling alley. Now all closed down liao. That night we went and had a great feast bbq-ing and finally we were the few last customers around, then the boss came to us and happily passed us two complimentary potong ice cream and "said xiao mei mei xiao di, eat slowly ah don't worry". We thank him and while we continue to feast we notice him clearing up some tables as usual then all of a sudden the staff all disappeared. It was 1am or later. Guess what we haven't even foot the bill! We also pay at the end of the meal, that's their practice. 😱It was really one of our "more for less" that we can never forget and still talk about until today. 🤤 #BallinWithGrab #Grab

The price for catching movies can be hefty during season with excellent films. To get more for less, simply plan the movie timings one after another, buy two tickets and head to Shaw Theatre at Nex. There is only one exit to leave the movie complex and the route allows you to simple walk into the theatre next door for the following show without anyone checking. Great way to spend an entire afternoon with the little you have. Even better if the ride to Nex with Cindy Chan is covered by Grab!

I bought a wall clock with a cute cartoon face design from an online marketplace platform Lynette Yoo, my sister, started  assembling the parts of the wall clock with me after receiving it. We got very frustrated after trying unsuccessfully to affix the second hand and the minute hand to the clock face for an hour. I called the seller's contact and was taught over the phone but were still unsuccessful. At the end, he got my address and presented himself at my doorstep hours later with a fully assembled wall clock. I offered to return him the clock on hand but he refused and just left. Undeterred, Lynette and I tried again trying to assemble it without fearing of breaking the hands since another one has been given to me. We were finally successful. We felt bad getting two wall clocks for the price of one. I went to the marketplace platform and left him a compliment, thanking him for his initiative and fast response to my requests. We had hoped for assistance via phone but got a second clock, assembled instead is really beyond our expectations. Till today, both wall clocks are still working well in the living room and bedroom.  #BallinWithGrab

It was during Christmas eve, the last day of delivering happiness campaign. While i was pushing a trolley of old books to the driver, i fell, dislocated and fractured my elbow. Having seen that, he insisted on waiting for me to go home to take my IC, send me to A&E , while he load the books into his car. When we reached the hospital, he refused to accept any money. It was because of his kindness that i received prompt medical attention. He is none other than Mr. Muhammad Yazid Bin Alwi, a man with big heart. I would like to take this opportunity to thank him and i hope he will be rewarded too!  *liked and shared this post*

It was raining heavily and I just took a ride back from work to home. Driver arrived earlier than I expected and he waited for me at the loading bay with an umbrella to shelter me to this car. Upon boarding this car, he even offered me tissue to wipe the rain off my arms. Played my favourite radio station and turned on the heater as he saw me sneezing. What more can I ask for? Thank you very much Mr Ang Boon Seng in a Toyota Altis, deeply appreciated.

Would like to share on this Grabhitch driver who made my night yesterday!!!   Like a usual night on 25 Jan, I took a grab car back home from my mum's place to my own after picking up my toddler. I was pleasantly surprised to get an instant text from the driver that he would be earlier than the booked timing! He told me no worries and he will wait for me with his easily recognisable car with pepsi decal. At times it is hard to recognise the car late night and I appreciate that little gesture.  Headed down with my toddler early since I was tired from the long day and can't wait to be home. Although it was a short journey with slight drizzling, it was an enjoyable chat with the driver and my toddler was also listening attentively.  Bided goodbye and upon reaching home, I realised that my mum's home-baked Kueh Lapis cake was left in the car. I didn't want to disturb the driver since it's so late at night. In 5 mins, I got a text with three missed calls if the cake belongs to me. Didn't want to inconvenience him but the driver insisted on returning it to me. In 5 mins, the driver was back to where he alighted me. The cakes were back in my hands!  Thank you Mr Vicvic Ang of SJU 3029U for your kindness and taking the trouble to return my items to me. It may just be a small gesture for you but to me, you ended a stranger's long day so well!  Having to juggle motherhood and full-time work can be tiring with time being of essence, so Grab taxis have been my best friend. And it's drivers like Mr Vic that keep me going/clicking all the time. Happy new year to grab & grab drivers! :)

2 days ago, it was raining heavily. I called grabcar to go to work. As it was raining heavily, my driver saw me and make the initiative to bring a umbrella to me. When I reached my destination, even though the rain is not very heavy already, he still make the initiative to sheltered me to my workplace with the umbrella.  Overall, it is a pleasant trip that I had received so far. My driver services was so good and friendly throughout the trip. My driver name was Teo Ah Guan, carplate no. SJG5820L. I would like to thanks him for the services that he had provided and wishing him a great happy Chinese new year !

Few months ago my father in law was in ICU on his last stage and he wants to see me and I was unable to get any cab on road and by booking.. eventually I tried grab car and within seconds I got a ride and driver arrive within few min and I told him my emergency 🚨 and he started to drive and without any stop and without any objection he drive me straight to Hospital and at the point of time I could not even thank him face to face I get down and ran to ICU.. but I gave his 5 star and also feedback on his kindness and help which he done for me...  till today I am feeling thankful .. god bless him..

liked and shared this post already! :) It was during peak hours and there was jam at serangoon road when i booked grab at mustafa centre. However, he kept apologized to us and still managed to get us to the destination safely. He is also a friendly driver that keep us engaged in conversation and not make the car ride boring. He is Mr. Mohamed Yassin S/O Abdul aziz and was driving a mitsubishi lancer. Thank you Mr Yassin and hope you have a great chinese new year :)

I have many good experiences w friendly Grab Drivers and to cite which particular incident is tough, am really grateful they send me to the destination as safe as they can, be it via Grabshare, Grab Taxi or Grab Hitch, so all deserve a compliment from bottom of my heart plus the generous promo codes! 👏🏼   Perhaps I will just share the most recent a few wkends ago, a friend who was traveling in a Grab car with me, her elder daughter and her young baby, requested the driver to drop at one more stop along the way, which we forgot to tell him about. He patiently sent us there and told us how to inform Grab when we book next time. Also, happen that my friend's elder daughter accidentally left her handphone at the back car seat's door holder. We did not realized it until we have all gotten down the car and it has been driven away for awhile. I called up the driver immediately and he was very kind and stopped at the roadside he was already driving on, and searched for the handphone, while I was waiting on the line to hear good news hopefully that the handphone was still around and thank God it was. But as the driver couldn't come back to where my friend stays to return the hand phone that day due to urgent valid reason; and he kindly offered to hold it and return it to my friend the following day, arranging a convenient place for them to meet and return the handphone to them. He was very honest and fast to respond and willing to directly arrange w my friend on the handphone return, which was done smoothly.   I would like to thank Mr Heng Siew Kwang driving SJW 5778S for his honesty and professionalism to us. We really need to be grateful for faithful service people like them to make the world a better place! 👏🏼

We just landed from a 24 hrs flight from Canada to Singapore, me, my husband and my baby! We had like 3 big lugagges and 2 small luggages plus a stroller. We que in the taxi cab, but they didn't accepted us because of our lugagges. It was so stressful and we were very tired, and no choice I have to pay extra for the lugagges. Then I browse my phone and took my chance using grab... and tada! I only book for a grabcar, just after 2 mins, he called me, and i immediately asked if he can accept our booking considering our number of lugagges... he immediately said why not?! I was so relieved... he saved us and made our day! And i felt we were indeed HOME! Thanks again to our grab driver Mr. Ho Kim Cherng! Hope you can read this also! More power Grab! Happy CNY to all!

I took a grab taxi to a Christmas party at a friend's house, partied and ate my fill. When leaving for home, I realised my wallet was not with me and I panicked- I probably left it in the grab car! And it contained my cards, IC and a significant sum of money (for christmas shopping)! I called the Grab service, who gave my contact to the driver, but needless to say the waiting for that call was tense.  An hour later, the driver phoned and asked where I was and he would drive all the way just to meet me to return it! I have never met such an honest cab driver who really went the extra mile to deliver my wallet to me, and when he returned it I nearly cried. Thank you so much Mr Rosmawan Bin Ramli! I wish I knew your carplate number. You really made my Christmas :)

My driver Eddy Tan SGV9957G drove me on 17 Dec 2016 from woodlands all the way to the east and helped me carry 3 extremely heavy boxes of personal items from my lift lobby into his car. I thought most drivers would have grumbled about having to deal with extra load but he even carried the boxes effortlessly to my destination's lift lobby with his big smile again and I felt he was very genuine the whole time.  I've encountered my fair share of bad drivers but Eddy definitely deserves some recognition! Thanks again!!

GrabShare's ERP charges are totally unfair to passenger B for Scenario 3. Why should passenger B need to share or even pay ERP charges if picked up within ERP zones? With UberPool, UberX or GrabCar, in such a scenario when the rider is picked up inside ERP zones, no surcharges are levied, if I'm not mistaken.   If passenger A's pickup AND drop off points are both outside the ERP zones, why should he/she pay the ERP charges? It should be borne 💯% by the driver as it's not A's fault or requirement to enter the ERP zone. Again passenger B is not liable either as when B is being picked up within the CBD zone, previously they're not assessed with any toll charges at all under UberPool, UberX or GrabCar unless they again enter through another ERP zone gantry for any reason. The driver wants to pick up an extra fare inside the CBD zone so should bear the ERP toll.  This does not however apply when ERP is imcurred on highways and both passenger A & B are INSIDE the car. Both parties should however be asked by the driver for permission to take the tolled highway option when other non toll optional routes are available for use, BOTH passengers A and B Must agree too of course.  Let's see what Grab says when queried on these assertions of mine⁉😡

I do grab hitch sometimes and i would like to share some tips for pax to have a better chance to get a hitch ride:  1) answer the phone call when the driver call u. I wont proceed to pick a pax if he or she doesnt answer the call. Many pax do not cancel their booking even when they no longer need it as there is no penalty not to do so. So i don't want to make a wasted trip. Already even with a confirmation over the phone, i have on 3 occasions arrived at the pick up points n the pax didn't turn up n didnt answer the calls. I called grab to ask them to blacklist these idiots. Some pax are also strange. They dunt answer call but sms the driver instead. Driver is driving. How to text n drive at the same time?  2) indicate your address clearly. Dunt just put postal code. Drivers have many hitch requests. We won't waste time to check where is your postal codes   3) Hitch is different from grab car. We are not a cheaper version of grab car. Don't treat us like grab drivers. And in any case, pax should respect grab drivers who are making an honest living.  I have a friend who is a full time grab driver. He took a booking from a certain FT. When he arrived, the pax scolded him and asked why he was 2 minutes later than the time indicated in the apps? He then asked my friend if he knows how much he earns n wasting time is wasting his money.  Seriously, i dunt think any driver care about how much any pax earn.  They are just there to bring u from point A to point B safely.  In any case, if u r earning a lot, u shouldnt be booking a grab economy. U should have your own luxury car with a personal chauffeur. I took a booking from a FT. His fare was only $5. He behaved like he is paying $50. If i ever see his name again, i wont take his booking.
